@startuml DailyProblemClassification_SP_PAClassification
title CTS_ProblemAccountsClassification_Daily - Detailed Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF9C4
skinparam noteBorderColor #FBC02D
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #FFE0B2
skinparam activityBorderColor #FF6F00

start

:Stored Procedure Called;
note right
  **SP Name**: CTS_ProblemAccountsClassification_Daily
  **Database**: bodb_VR2Model.wsv_cts (SQL Server)
  **Timeout**: 1200 seconds (20 minutes)
  **Parameters**: Customer list from queue
  **Called From**: ProblemAccountServices.GetProblemAccountLosingClassification()
  
  **Function ID**: ProblemDailyJob
  **Long Timeout Reason**: Complex PA calculations
end note

partition "Input Processing" {
  :Receive Customer List;
  note right
    **Input**: PADailyScanFromQueueEntity[]
    - CustID (long)
    - DWSportType (int)
    
    **Source**: DailyPAQueue
  end note

  :Parse Customer IDs;
  :Create temp table #TempCustomers;
  note right
    **Temp Table**:
    - CustID
    - DWSportType
    - Used for joining with transaction data
  end note
}

partition "Get Customer Transaction Data" {
  :Query customer betting history;
  note right
    **Data Sources**:
    - Bet transactions (completed bets)
    - Winloss records
    - Turnover records
    - Performance period: Last 30 days (configurable)
    
    **Joined Tables**:
    - CustomerTransaction
    - BetDetails
    - SettlementInfo
  end note

  :Filter by date range;
  note right
    **Date Filter**:
    - Performance period: 30/60/90 days
    - Only settled bets
    - Exclude cancelled/void bets
  end note
}

partition "Calculate Losing Performance" {
  :Calculate Turnover per customer;
  note right
    **Turnover Calculation**:
    - SUM(BetAmount) per CustID
    - In RM (Malaysia Ringgit)
    - All sports aggregated
    - Decimal precision: 2
    
    **Formula**:
    TurnoverRM = SUM(BetAmount)
  end note

  :Calculate Winloss per customer;
  note right
    **Winloss Calculation**:
    - SUM(Winloss) per CustID
    - Negative = Customer loss (good for company)
    - Positive = Customer win (bad for company)
    - In RM
    
    **Formula**:
    WinlossRM = SUM(Winloss)
    
    **PA Focus**:
    - Looking for large losses (negative winloss)
    - High loss = Potential PA
  end note

  :Calculate Bet Count per customer;
  note right
    **Bet Count**:
    - COUNT(BetID) per CustID
    - Total number of bets
    - Indicates betting frequency
    
    **Formula**:
    BetCount = COUNT(BetID)
  end note

  :Calculate Active Days per customer;
  note right
    **Active Days**:
    - COUNT(DISTINCT BetDate) per CustID
    - Number of days with bets
    - Indicates betting consistency
    
    **Formula**:
    ActiveDays = COUNT(DISTINCT BetDate)
  end note

  :Get Performance Time;
  note right
    **Performance Time**:
    - Date range of calculation
    - Start date and end date
    - Used for historical tracking
  end note
}

partition "Apply PA Classification Rules" {
  :Determine PA Category;
  note right
    **PA Categorization Logic**:
    Based on losing performance thresholds
    
    **Category Rules**:
    1. **PA (Problem Account)**:
       - High loss amount (e.g., > RM 10,000)
       - High turnover (e.g., > RM 50,000)
       - Consistent betting (ActiveDays > 15)
       - Significant losing trend
       
    2. **PotentialPA**:
       - Medium loss amount (e.g., RM 5,000-10,000)
       - Medium turnover (e.g., RM 20,000-50,000)
       - Moderate betting activity
       - Developing losing pattern
       
    **Thresholds**:
    - Configurable per sport
    - Adjustable per company policy
    - Based on historical data
  end note

  if (High loss amount?) then (yes)
    if (High turnover?) then (yes)
      if (Consistent betting?) then (yes)
        :Assign CategoryID = PA;
        note right
          **PA Customer**:
          - High risk
          - Requires monitoring
          - Probation period applies
          - Special handling
        end note
      else (no)
        :Assign CategoryID = PotentialPA;
      endif
    else (no)
      :Assign CategoryID = PotentialPA;
    endif
  elseif (Medium loss amount?) then (yes)
    :Assign CategoryID = PotentialPA;
    note right
      **PotentialPA Customer**:
      - Medium risk
      - Watch for escalation
      - May become PA
      - Monitor closely
    end note
  else (no)
    :No PA classification;
    note right
      **Below thresholds**:
      - Not classified as PA
      - May be removed from queue
      - Normal customer
    end note
  endif
}

partition "Build Result" {
  :Build ProblemAccountLosingClassificationEntity[];
  note right
    **Result Entity**:
    - CustID
    - CategoryID (PA/PotentialPA)
    - TurnoverRM
    - WinlossRM (negative for loss)
    - BetCount
    - ActiveDays
    - PerformanceTime
    - CategoryName
    - Other PA metrics
  end note

  :Include additional PA metrics;
  note right
    **Additional Metrics**:
    - Average bet size
    - Win rate (%)
    - Largest single loss
    - Consecutive losing days
    - Sport-specific metrics
    - Risk score
  end note
}

:Return ProblemAccountLosingClassificationEntity[];
note right
  **Return to Service Layer**:
  - Used for InsertProblemAccountProbationClassification
  - Contains all PA classification data
  - Ready for database insertion
  
  **Next Steps**:
  - Batch processing
  - Insert into CTSCustomerClassification
  - Insert PA logic
  - Push to MainDB
end note

:Log Execution;
note right
  **Logging**:
  - Customer count processed
  - PA count identified
  - PotentialPA count identified
  - Execution time
  - Any errors/warnings
end note

stop

note bottom
  **PA Classification Summary**:
  
  **Purpose**: Identify customers with significant losing performance
  **Criteria**: Turnover, Winloss, BetCount, ActiveDays
  **Categories**: PA (high risk), PotentialPA (medium risk)
  **Action**: Probation period, monitoring, special handling
  
  **Business Logic**:
  - PA customers are high-risk for company
  - Large losses indicate potential issues
  - Requires careful monitoring and management
  - Probation period to observe behavior
  - May require manual review
  
  **Performance Considerations**:
  - Complex calculation (20 min timeout)
  - Large dataset processing
  - Multiple joins and aggregations
  - Indexed tables for efficiency
  - Batch processing recommended
  
  **Thresholds (Example)**:
  | Category | TurnoverRM | WinlossRM (Loss) | ActiveDays |
  |----------|-----------|------------------|------------|
  | PA | > 50,000 | < -10,000 | > 15 |
  | PotentialPA | > 20,000 | < -5,000 | > 10 |
end note

@enduml

